  "text": "For example, [CITATION_1] introduce a dividend model featuring intrinsic bubbles that are nonlinearly driven by exogenous fundamental determinants of asset prices. The linear model can also be extended by using a log-linear approximation of the present-value relation (see, for example, Campbell (1991)). Thus, the asset price behavior can be modeled without imposing restrictions on expected returns.",
